endpoint : `/api/v1${endpoint}`;\n        const url = `${API_BASE_URL}${normalizedEndpoint}`;\n        try {\n            const headers = await this.getAuthHeaders();\n            const response = await fetch(url, {\n                method: 'GET',\n                headers\n            });\n            if (!response.ok) {\n                const errorData = await response.json().catch(()=>({}));\n                throw new APIError(errorData.detail || `HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`, response.status, errorData);\n            }\n            // Create download link\n            const blob = await response.blob();\n            const downloadUrl = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n            const link = document.createElement('a');\n            link.href = downloadUrl;\n            link.download = filename;\n            document.body.appendChild(link);\n            link.click();\n            document.body.removeChild(link);\n            window.URL.revokeObjectURL(downloadUrl);\n        } catch (error) {\n            if (error instanceof APIError) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            throw new APIError(error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Network error', 0);\n        }\n    }\n    async upload(endpoint, file, additionalData) {\n        const normalizedEndpoint = endpoint.startsWith('/api') ? endpoint : `/api/v1${endpoint}`;\n        const url = `${API_BASE_URL}${normalizedEndpoint}`;\n        try {\n            const headers = await this.getAuthHeaders();\n            // Remove Content-Type header to let browser set it with boundary for FormData\n            delete headers['Content-Type'];\n            const formData = new FormData();\n            formData.append('file', file);\n            // Add any additional data\n            if (additionalData) {\n                Object.entries(additionalData).forEach(([key, value])=>{\n                    formData.append(key, String(value));\n                });\n            }\n            const response = await fetch(url, {\n                method: 'POST',\n                headers,\n                body: formData\n            });\n            if (!response.ok) {\n                const errorData = await response.json().catch(()=>({}));\n                throw new APIError(errorData.detail || `HTTP ${response.status}: ${response.statusText}`, response.status, errorData);\n            }\n            // Handle empty responses\n            const contentType = response.headers.get('content-type');\n            if (contentType && contentType.includes('application/json')) {\n                return response.json();\n            }\n            return response.text();\n        } catch (error) {\n            if (error instanceof APIError) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            throw new APIError(error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Network error', 0);\n        }\n    }\n    // Public convenience methods for unauthenticated endpoints\n    async publicGet(endpoint, options) {\n        let url = endpoint;\n        // Add query parameters if provided\n        if (options?.params) {\n            const searchParams = new URLSearchParams();\n            Object.entries(options.params).forEach(([key, value])=>{\n                if (value !== undefined && value !== null) {\n                    searchParams.append(key, String(value));\n                }\n            });\n            const queryString = searchParams.toString();\n            if (queryString) {\n                url += (endpoint.includes('?') ? '&' : '?') + queryString;\n            }\n        }\n        return this.publicRequest(url, {\n            method: 'GET'\n        });\n    }\n    async publicPost(endpoint, data) {\n        return this.publicRequest(endpoint, {\n            method: 'POST',\n            body: data ? JSON.stringify(data) : undefined\n        });\n    }\n}\nconst apiClient = new APIClient();\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# non-profit or government organization');\n        }\n        if (employeeCount < 10 && annualRevenue === 'Over £100M') {\n            warnings.push('High revenue with small team may indicate specialized or high-value services');\n        }\n        return warnings;\n    },\n    // Validate framework selection based on business characteristics\n    validateFrameworkSelection: (profile)=>{\n        const recommendations = [];\n        if (profile.handles_personal_data && !profile.existing_frameworks?.includes('GDPR') && !profile.planned_frameworks?.includes('GDPR')) {\n            recommendations.push('Consider GDPR compliance for personal data handling');\n        }\n        if (profile.processes_payments && !profile.existing_frameworks?.includes('PCI DSS') && !profile.planned_frameworks?.includes('PCI DSS')) {\n            recommendations.push('Consider PCI DSS compliance for payment processing');\n        }\n        if (profile.stores_health_data && !profile.existing_frameworks?.includes('HIPAA') && !profile.planned_frameworks?.includes('HIPAA')) {\n            recommendations.push('Consider HIPAA compliance for health data');\n        }\n        return recommendations;\n    },\n    // Validate technology stack completeness\n    validateTechnologyStack: (stack)=>{\n        const suggestions = [];\n        if (!stack.cloud_providers?.length && !stack.saas_tools?.length) {\n            suggestions.push('Adding technology information helps with compliance recommendations');\n        }\n        if (stack.cloud_providers?.length && !stack.development_tools?.length) {\n            suggestions.push('Consider adding development tools for complete technology profile');\n        }\n        return suggestions;\n    }\n};\n// Error message formatting\nfunction formatValidationErrors(error) {\n    return error.errors.map((err)=>({\n            field: err.path.join('.'),\n            message: err.message\n        }));\n}\n//#
